01:32:55,301 --> 01:32:58,697
Well, we have relatives all the way
in Glasgow and Portsmouth!

1339
01:32:58,771 --> 01:33:00,753
[ Laughing, Chattering ]

1340
01:33:00,826 --> 01:33:04,418
- Mom, Dad, Tony's lying.
- Lying?

1341
01:33:04,488 --> 01:33:07,247
We're not
getting married.

1342
01:33:07,313 --> 01:33:10,972
<i>Tony only said that to help me,
but I'm not lying anymore.</i>

1343
01:33:12,453 --> 01:33:16,691
- I played in the final today, and we won.
- How? When?

1344
01:33:16,756 --> 01:33:19,517
I wasn't going to go,
but Dad let me.

1345
01:33:20,964 --> 01:33:23,559
And it was brilliant.

1346
01:33:24,657 --> 01:33:27,155
I played the best ever.

1347
01:33:27,227 --> 01:33:29,307
And I was happy...

1348
01:33:29,380 --> 01:33:31,721
because I wasn't sneaking off
and lying to you.

1349
01:33:33,331 --> 01:33:37,436
I didn't ask to be good at football.
Guru Nanak must have blessed me.

1350
01:33:39,496 --> 01:33:41,894
Anyway, there was a scout
from America there today...

1351
01:33:41,970 --> 01:33:45,561
<i>and he's offered me a place
at a top university...</i>

1352
01:33:45,630 --> 01:33:49,256
with a free scholarship and a chance
to play football professionally.

1353
01:33:50,931 --> 01:33:54,139
I really want to go.

1354
01:33:54,207 --> 01:33:58,566
And if I can't tell you what I want now,
then I'll never be happy whatever I do.

1355
01:33:58,639 --> 01:34:02,066
You let her leave
her sister's wedding...

1356
01:34:02,139 --> 01:34:04,637
<i>to go to a football match.!</i>

1357
01:34:04,710 --> 01:34:07,787
Maybe you could handle
her long face. I could not.

1358
01:34:07,858 --> 01:34:10,199
I didn't have the heart
to stop her.

1359
01:34:10,266 --> 01:34:14,732
And that's why she's ready
to go all the way to America now!

1360
01:34:14,860 --> 01:34:18,617
<i>- [ Woman Panicking In Panjabi ]
- [ Whispers ] She's dead meat.</i>

1361
01:34:18,683 --> 01:34:21,694
<i>- [ Tony's Mum, Panjabi ]
- [ Tony ] It's all right, Mum.Just leave it.</i>

1362
01:34:25,685 --> 01:34:28,696
When those bloody English cricket players
threw me out of their club...

1363
01:34:28,768 --> 01:34:31,046
<i>like a dog...</i>

1364
01:34:33,200 --> 01:34:35,895
I never complained.

1365
01:34:35,963 --> 01:34:39,718
On the contrary, I vowed
that I would never play again.

1366
01:34:39,784 --> 01:34:42,577
Who suffered? Me.

1367
01:34:45,503 --> 01:34:47,713
But I don't want
Jessie to suffer.

1368
01:34:50,449 --> 01:34:53,909
I don't want her to make the same mistakes
that her father made of...

1369
01:34:53,981 --> 01:34:57,343
accepting life
or accepting situations.

1370
01:34:59,602 --> 01:35:02,098
I want her to fight.

1371
01:35:03,199 --> 01:35:05,346
<i>And I want her to win.</i>

1372
01:35:06,926 --> 01:35:10,287
Because I've seen her playing.
She's-- She's brilliant.

1373
01:35:14,409 --> 01:35:18,066
I don't think anybody has
the right of stopping her.

1374
01:35:21,571 --> 01:35:23,553
[ Sniffling ]

1375
01:35:25,683 --> 01:35:31,070
Two daughters made happy on one day.
What else can a father ask for?

1376
01:35:31,142 --> 01:35:34,472
At least I've taught her full Indian dinner.
The rest is up to God.

1377
01:35:34,548 --> 01:35:36,824
[ Both Laugh ]

1378
01:35:36,892 --> 01:35:39,137
<i># [ Woman Vocalizing ]</i>

1379
01:35:42,481 --> 01:35:44,398
<i>Joe.!</i>

1380
01:35:46,078 --> 01:35:49,835
I'm going!
They said I could go!

1381
01:35:56,967 --> 01:36:00,043
<i>- [ Men ] Oi, oi, oi.!
- I'm sorry. I forgot.</i>

1382
01:36:00,114 --> 01:36:04,384
- [ Pants ]
- That's okay now. I'm not your coach anymore.

1383
01:36:05,638 --> 01:36:07,883
We can do what we want.

1384
01:36:09,460 --> 01:36:12,790
-Joe.
- Your dad's not here, is he?

1385
01:36:14,695 --> 01:36:17,005
I'm sorry,Joe.
I can't.

1386
01:36:22,630 --> 01:36:24,610
I thought you wanted--

1387
01:36:29,501 --> 01:36:33,060
Letting me go is a really big step
for my mom and dad.

1388
01:36:34,514 --> 01:36:37,842
I don't know how they'd survive
if I told them about you too.

1389
01:36:46,975 --> 01:36:48,956
[ Exhales Sharply ]

1390
01:36:50,573 --> 01:36:54,327
I guess there's not much point,
with you going to America anyway.

1391
01:36:54,394 --> 01:36:56,377
Is there?

1392
01:36:57,349 --> 01:36:59,496
<i># [ Continues ]</i>

1393
01:37:34,028 --> 01:37:36,854
- Mum, it's not perfume, is it?
- No. It's not what you think.

1394
01:37:36,919 --> 01:37:39,350
- Go on.
- It was your mum's idea.

1395
01:37:39,425 --> 01:37:41,285
It was.

1396
01:37:41,351 --> 01:37:43,148
- [ Gasps ]
- Hmm?

1397
01:37:43,215 --> 01:37:46,225
- Oh, thank you so much.
- [ Laughing ]

1398
01:37:46,297 --> 01:37:48,827
Make sure you keep this
by your bed all the time, huh?

1399
01:37:48,899 --> 01:37:51,593
<i>And phone Papu Uncle in Canada
as soon as you land.</i>

1400
01:37:51,661 --> 01:37:53,774
At least there's
some family close by.

1401
01:37:53,845 --> 01:37:57,536
Excuse me. It's getting really late.
You'd better board the plane.

1402
01:37:57,604 --> 01:38:00,483
<i>-Just--
- [ P.A. Announcements, Indistinct ]</i>

1403
01:38:04,124 --> 01:38:06,499
<i>Jess.!</i>

1404
01:38:07,785 --> 01:38:09,930
Don't worry.
That's her coach.

1405
01:38:11,383 --> 01:38:13,365
What are you doing here?

1406
01:38:13,438 --> 01:38:18,191
[ Sighs ] They offered me the job
coaching the men's side.

1407
01:38:18,256 --> 01:38:20,369
No more pulling pints.

1408
01:38:20,440 --> 01:38:23,551
- That's great,Joe.
- Yeah. I turned them down.

1409
01:38:23,620 --> 01:38:27,376
- What? Why did you--
- They're gonna let me coach the girls' side.

1410
01:38:27,443 --> 01:38:29,939
They want us to turn pro
next year.

1411
01:38:30,011 --> 01:38:33,439
- Wow!
- Can't keep losin' all my best players
to the Yanks, now, can I?

1412
01:38:33,512 --> 01:38:36,820
That's brilliant,Joe.
You should tell your dad, you know.

1413
01:38:36,886 --> 01:38:38,997
I already did.

1414
01:38:39,069 --> 01:38:41,149
<i>[ Mrs. Bhamra ]
Are you sure we're doing the right thing?</i>

1415
01:38:41,220 --> 01:38:43,619
Whatever God has written
for her will happen.Just relax.

1416
01:38:43,694 --> 01:38:46,869
<i>Maybe after they trained you up,
I'll sign ya, if I can afford ya.</i>

1417
01:38:46,937 --> 01:38:49,698
- Ah, you wish. [ Laughs ]
- [ Laughs ]

1418
01:38:49,765 --> 01:38:53,837
Look. I can't let you go
without knowin'.

1419
01:38:53,907 --> 01:38:57,216
What?

1420
01:38:57,281 --> 01:39:02,220
That even with the distance--
and the concerns of your family--

1421
01:39:02,291 --> 01:39:05,270
we might still
have something.

1422
01:39:05,343 --> 01:39:07,718
Don't you think?

1423
01:39:10,062 --> 01:39:12,243
<i># [ Woman Singing ]</i>

1424
01:39:16,134 --> 01:39:18,246
<i>Oh, my God.!
Dad, it's Beckham.!</i>

1425
01:39:18,317 --> 01:39:20,980
Oh, it's a sign!

1426
01:39:22,429 --> 01:39:25,189
Jess, look!
It's Becks!

1427
01:39:42,375 --> 01:39:46,962
- I'm back at Christmas.
We'll tackle my mom and dad then.
- Yeah.

1428
01:39:50,020 --> 01:39:52,877
Okay. I'd better go.

1429
01:39:58,820 --> 01:40:01,512
-Jules. Take care of yourself.
- All right. I'll see you later, mate.

1430
01:40:01,582 --> 01:40:04,046
- Have a good time, love. Keep an eye out.
- Oh, and you.

1431
01:40:04,119 --> 01:40:07,876
Hey, you two. You're gonna miss this plane.
Ticket. Go. Go.

1432
01:40:07,941 --> 01:40:10,437
Bye, dear.

1433
01:40:10,510 --> 01:40:13,139
[ Muttering Good-byes ]

1434
01:40:13,209 --> 01:40:16,416
- Come on.
- Bye, sweetheart.

1435
01:40:19,824 --> 01:40:23,187
<i># [ Man Singing ]</i>

1436
01:40:23,262 --> 01:40:27,718
- Hi.
- Hi. Nice to meet you.

1437
01:40:27,791 --> 01:40:29,740
Good-bye!

1438
01:40:36,944 --> 01:40:38,861
[ Muttering ]

1439
01:40:40,187 --> 01:40:42,334
Come on.
Let's have a look.

1440
01:40:43,882 --> 01:40:46,892
- Hey, hey!
- Hey! Wow. Look at that.

1441
01:40:46,965 --> 01:40:48,947
<i># [ Continues ]</i>

1442
01:40:58,559 --> 01:41:00,476
<i>[ Thudding ]</i>

1443
01:41:03,923 --> 01:41:06,552
[ Chattering ]

1444
01:41:16,000 --> 01:41:17,861
- Yes!
- [ Muttering ]

1445
01:41:17,926 --> 01:41:19,789
- Yes!
- No, no, no.

1446
01:41:19,854 --> 01:41:22,482
- Oh, yes, yes, yes.
- No, no, no.

1447
01:41:39,158 --> 01:41:41,020
<i># [ Chorus ]</i>

1448
01:41:48,312 --> 01:41:51,006
?? [ Panjabi ]

1449
01:42:45,546 --> 01:42:47,562
Whoo!

1450
01:43:00,129 --> 01:43:03,719
[ Bleep ] I forgot the line. [ Laughs ]

1451
01:43:05,653 --> 01:43:07,515
[ Sustained Bleep ]

1452
01:43:07,581 --> 01:43:11,139
Heh! Wait.

1453
01:43:57,749 --> 01:43:59,645
[ Indistinct ] Oh! [ Bleeping ]

1454
01:44:03,562 --> 01:44:05,962
[ Bleep ]

1455
01:44:13,101 --> 01:44:15,020
[ Laughing ]

1456
01:44:17,181 --> 01:44:19,098
<i>[ Woman ]
Excellent. Thank you.</i>

1457
01:44:19,172 --> 01:44:21,768
- Laters!
- [ All Laugh ]

1458
01:44:29,868 --> 01:44:32,430
<i># [ Man Singing
In Panjabi ]</i>

